4|S|28|20|E|display=inline|name=Warmbaths}}\n|-\n| [[AFB Waterkloof]] {{!!}} 264 {{!!}} FAWK {{!!}} {{coord|25|50|S|28|13|E|display=inline}}\n|-\n| [[Welkom]] {{!!}} 346 {{!!}} FAWM {{!!}} {{coord|28|00|S|26|40|E|display=inline|name=Welkom}}\n|-\n| [[Wepener]] {{!!}} 550 {{!!}} {{!!}} {{coord|29|44|S|27|2|E|display=inline|name=Wepener}}\n|-\n| [[Willowmore]] {{!!}} 832 {{!!}} {{!!}} {{coord|33|17|S|23|30|E|display=inline|name=Willowmore}}\n|}\n{{hidden end}}\n\n=== Weather radar ===\nNear real-time (''~5 minutes delay'') [[weather radar]] is available for most of the country,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://metsys.weathersa.co.za/RadarGeneral.htm |title=Radar Home |publisher=South African Weather Service |access-date=2008-12-04 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081218155922/http://metsys.weathersa.co.za/RadarGeneral.htm |archive-date=18 December 2008 |df=dmy }}</ref> even within the [[Kruger National Park]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.krugerpark.co.za/krugerpark-times-4-5-radar-station-24179.html|title=Radar Station Completed|author=Nick Zambatis and Lynette Strauss |publisher=Siyabona Africa Travel|accessdate=2008-12-04}}</ref>\n\n=== Marine weather buoys ===\nBetween 30 and 40 drifting weather buoys are deployed annually.<ref name=\"gough\"/>\n\n== Weather modification ==\nThe SAWS, in cooperation with a number of other entities, is actively involved in [[weather control]] research under the ''South African National Precipitation Research and Rainfall Enhancement Programme'', specifically with the ''Bethlehem Precipitation Research Project''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://metsys.weathersa.co.za/bprp_bg |title=The Bethlehem Precipitation Research Project |publisher=South African Weather Service |access-date=2008-12-04 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090114223947/http://metsys.weathersa.co.za/bprp_bg |archive-date=14 January 2009 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wrc.org.za/archives/news%20archive/2005/imc-NPRP-SAREP%20(nov05).ppt|title=South African National Precipitation Research and Rainfall Enhancement Programme (NPRP-SAREP)  1990 - 2000|publisher=South African Water Research Commission|accessdate=2008-12-04}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[South African National Antarctic Programme]]\n* [[World Meteorological Organization]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{official website}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20081218155922/http://metsys.weathersa.co.za/RadarGeneral.htm Near real-time weather radar]\n\n{{National Meteorological Organisations}}\n\n[[Category:Governmental meteorological agencies in Africa|South African Weather Service]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Meteorological agency of South Africa}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2012}}\n{{Use South African English|date=August 2012}}\nThe '''South African Weather Service''' (SAWS) is the meteorological service under the [[South Africa|South African]] government's [[Department of Environmental Affairs and Tourism]].  SAWS is a member of the [[World Meteorological Organization]].  The agency is similar to the [[United States]]' [[National Weather Service]].\n\nUnder the '''South African Weather Service Act''' (No. 8 of 2001) effective 15 July 2001, SAWS became a public entity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.weathersa.co.za/Corporate/SAWSAct8_2001.jsp |title=S A Weather Service Act (8 of 2001) |date=29 June 2001 |publisher=The Presidency of South Africa |access-date=2008-12-04 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081203121341/http://www.weathersa.co.za/Corporate/SAWSAct8_2001.jsp |archive-date=3 December 2008 |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\n== Data acquisition ==\n\n=== Weather stations ===\nSouth Africa operates a significant number of weather stations in [[South Africa]] as well as stations at [[Gough Island]], [[Marion Island]] and [[Antarctica]] in cooperation with the [[South African National Antarctic Programme]].<ref name=\"gough\">{{cite web|url=http://gough.sanap.org.za/weather.html |title=Weather Program |publisher=[[South African National Antarctic Program]] |access-date=2008-12-04 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080828162943/http://gough.sanap.org.za/weather.html |archive-date=28 August 2008 |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\n{{hidden begin\n|title = List of South African Weather Stations <ref>{{cite web|url=http://weather.noaa.gov/tg/site.shtml|title=Meteorological Station Location Information|publisher=[[National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration]]|accessdate=2008-12-04}}</ref>\n|titlestyle  = text-align:left;background:#b0c4de;height:20px;padding:1px;\n|bodystyle  = text-align:left;\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Name\n! [[World Meteorological Organization|WMO #]]\n! [[International Civil Aviation Organization|ICAO]]\n! Location\n|-\n| [[Alexander Bay, Northern Cape|Alexander Bay]] {{!!}} 406 {{!!}} FAAB {{!!}} {{coord|28|34|S|16|32|E|display=inline|name=Alexander Bay}}\n|-\n| [[Aliwal North]] {{!!}} 546 {{!!}} FAAN {{!!}} {{coord|30|43|S|26|43|E|display=inline|name=Aliwal North}}\n|-\n| [[Babanango, KwaZulu-Natal|Babanango]] {{!!}} 488 {{!!}} {{!!}} {{coord|28|23|S|31|5|E|display=inline|name=Babanango}}\n|-\n| [[Beaufort West]] {{!!}} 728 {{!!}} FABY {{!!}} {{coord|32|21|S|22|35|E|display=inline|name=Beaufort West}}\n|-\n| [[Bethal]] {{!!}} 370 {{!!}} {{!!}} {{coord|26|27|S|29|29|E|display=inline|name=Bethal}}\n|-\n| [[Bethlehem Airport]] {{!!}} 461 {{!!}} FABM {{!!}} {{coord|28|15|S|28|20|E|display=inline|name=Bethlehem Airport}}\n|-\n| [[Bethlehem, Free State|Bethlehem]] {{!!}} 462 {{!!}} {{!!}} {{coord|28|10|S|28|46|E|display=inline|name=Bethlehem}}\n|-\n| [[Bhisho|Bisho]] Airport {{!!}} 752 {{!!}} {{!!}} {{coord|32|50|S|27|27|E|display=inline|name=Bisho Airport}}\n|-\n| [[Bloemfontein Airport]] {{!!}} 442 {{!!}} FABL {{!!}} {{coord|29|6|S|26|18|E|display=inline|name=Bloemfontein Airport}}\n|-\n| [[Calvinia]] {{!!}} 618 {{!!}} FACV {{!!}} {{coord