 the Australian states}}\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Post\n!Incumbent\n!Appointed\n|-\n| [[Governor of Queensland]]\n| {{sort|De Jersey|His Excellency [[Paul de Jersey]]}}\n| {{dts|29 July 2014}}\n|-\n| [[Governor of South Australia]]\n| {{sort|Le|His Excellency [[Hieu Van Le]]}}\n| {{dts|1 September 2014}}\n|-\n| [[Governor of Tasmania]]\n| {{sort|Warner|Her Excellency [[Kate Warner]]}}\n| {{dts|10 December 2014}}\n|-\n| [[Governor of Victoria]]\n| {{sort|Dessau|Her Excellency [[Linda Dessau]]}}\n| {{dts|1 July 2015}}\n|-\n| [[Governor of Western Australia]]\n| {{sort|Beazley, Kim|His Excellency [[Kim Beazley]]}}\n| {{dts|1 May 2018}}\n|-\n| [[Governor of New South Wales]]\n| {{sort|Beazley, Margaret|Her Excellency [[Margaret Beazley]]}}\n| {{dts|2 May 2019}}\n|-\n| [[Administrator of the Northern Territory]]\n| {{sort|OHalloran|Her Honour [[Vicki O'Halloran]]}}\n| {{dts|31 October 2017}}\n|-\n| [[Administrator of Norfolk Island]]\n| {{sort|Hutchinson|His Honour [[Eric Hutchinson (politician)|Eric Hutchinson]]}}\n| {{dts|1 April 2017}}\n|-\n| [[Australian Indian Ocean Territories|Administrator of Australian Indian Ocean Territories]]<br/> (Christmas Island and Cocos (Keeling) Islands)\n| {{sort|Griggs|Her Honour [[Natasha Griggs]]}}\n| {{dts|5 October 2017}}\n|}\n\n==Premiers and chief ministers of states and territories==\n{{Main|Premiers and chief ministers of the Australian states and territories}}\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Post\n!Incumbent\n!Political party\n!Appointed\n|-\n| [[Premier of New South Wales]]\n| {{sortname|Gladys|Berejiklian}} {{post-nominals|country=AUS|MP}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"| [[Liberal Party of Australia (New South Wales Division)|Liberal]]\n| {{dts|23 January 2017}}\n|-\n| [[Premier of Queensland]]\n| {{sortname|Annastacia|Palaszczuk}} {{post-nominals|country=AUS|MP}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"| [[Australian Labor Party (Queensland Branch)|Labor]]\n| {{dts|14 February 2015}}\n|-\n| [[Premier of South Australia]]\n| 